The paper discusses the security and privacy vulnerabilities in machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also explores the technical aspects of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for formal frameworks for security and privacy in machine learning, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
